<subSubSection pageId="62" pageNumber="1021" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1058,315,367]" pageId="62" pageNumber="1021">
E t y m o l o g y: The trivial name, 
<emphasis box="[544,603,316,337]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="1021">acara</emphasis>
, is a Greek name with a meaning of &quot;tiny&quot;; with reference to the small size of these beetles.
</paragraph>
